        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 5 at 5:43PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 543 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Caledonia, or 9 miles southwest of Vernon, moving northeast at 40
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sulligent, Pine Springs, Lamar County Airport, Crews, Bedford, Lamar
County Public Lake, Gattman, and Vernon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
